did.unittitle: Washington Office on Africa Records - Addendum B
did.abstract: This collection is an addendum to the publications, correspondence, reports, statements, and collected material documenting the work of the Washington Office on Africa found in Record Groups 105 and 105A. The Washington Office on Africa was founded in 1972 to support the movement for freedom from white-minority rule in southern Africa. Its activities have included the monitoring of Congressional legislation and executive policies and actions, as well as the publication of action alerts and other documentation designed to advance progressive legislation and policy on southern Africa. Supported by church bodies and unions, the WOA has worked in partnership with colleagues in Africa, the Africa advocacy community in the United States, and grassroots organizations concerned with various aspects of African affairs.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: Gift of the Washington Office on Africa, 2002.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Washington Office on Africa Records - Addendum B (RG 105B), Special Collections, Yale Divinity School Library.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: See the finding aid for Record Group 105.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Series I, Regional and Country Files, is divided subseries that reflect various geographical subdivisions. These files contain materials documenting political, social, and economic affairs in the regions and countries specified.
Series II, Issues, which contains material arranged alphabetically by issue, complements the geographically arranged files of Series I.
Series III, Advocacy, contains Washington Office on Africa publications, correspondence, and documentation of participation in groups and events related to the issues of concern to WOA.
Series IV, United States Policy, contains documentation related to U.S. politics and Congressional hearings, laws, and correspondence related to Africa issues.
